    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6211/1635: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-01">April 1,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. For Spruks<note n="64" xml:id="d278fn64">H. Charles Spruks, ceremonial
                        officer in the Division of Protocol; on special mission in South America for
                        repatriation of Axis diplomatic missions.</note> from Green. Department has
                    now concurred in German suggestion that national flag shall be painted on sides
                    and top deck of vessel in addition to other markings previously specified.</p>
                <p>It has also been agreed on basis reciprocity that German officials being
                    repatriated may take with them household effects except furniture so far as
                    those effects are packed or entrusted to responsible warehousing or storage
                    firms capable of preparing them for shipment and are ready in time for lading
                    aboard. Some of these effects may be shipped on <hi rend="italic">Etolin</hi> if
                    they are ready. [Green.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
